# CONTEXT CONTROL: MODE-BASED PLUGIN MANAGEMENT

## Default Behavior
Plugins are OFF by default. File-level context only.
This keeps 80% of interactions fast and focused.

## Mode Activation

### FIX MODE (Speed Priority)
**Triggers:** "bug fix", "quick fix", "fix this", "debug"
**Context:** Current file + direct imports only
**Plugins:** OFF (unless explicitly requested)
**Thinking:** Fast, surgical, no extended contemplation
**Goal:** Sub-10 second responses
**Ideal Plugins:** None (that's the point)

Example: "Fix this validation bug" → loads just that file + imports

### BUILD MODE (Full Context)
**Triggers:** "build", "new feature", "implement", "create"
**Context:** Full project tree + architecture docs
**Plugins:** AUTO-ON (Supabase, Drive, any configured integrations)
**Thinking:** Extended thinking enabled, architectural consideration
**Goal:** Comprehensive solutions with full system awareness
**Ideal Plugins:**
- Supabase (database schema & data)
- Google Drive (technical specs, PRDs)
- GitHub (repo context, issues)
- API documentation sources

Example: "Build the parking lot module" → loads everything

### DESIGN MODE (UX/Visual Priority)
**Triggers:** "design", "UI", "UX", "layout", "component", "styling"
**Context:** Design system docs + component library + brand guidelines
**Plugins:** ON for visual/design sources, OFF for live data
**Thinking:** Extended, creative, pattern-focused on user experience
**Goal:** Polished, on-brand, user-centered solutions
**Ideal Plugins:**
- Figma (design files, components, prototypes)
- Google Drive (brand guidelines, design specs, style guides)
- Screenshot/image analysis (for reference designs)
- Design system documentation (if separate from codebase)
- Vercel (for checking deployed visual state)

Example: "Design the dashboard cards" → loads Figma + brand guidelines + component library

### ARCHITECTURE MODE (System Design)
**Triggers:** "architecture", "system design", "data model", "plan the system"
**Context:** Architecture docs + schemas + type definitions + integration docs
**Plugins:** ON for Drive/docs, OFF for live data sources
**Thinking:** Extended, strategic, pattern-focused on system design
**Goal:** Detailed specifications and architectural decisions
**Ideal Plugins:**
- Google Drive (architecture docs, ADRs, technical RFCs)
- Database schema tools
- API documentation

Example: "Design the workflow orchestration system" → loads docs + schemas, skips DB

## Manual Plugin Override
At any time, explicitly request plugins:
- "with Supabase" → activates DB context
- "check Drive" → activates Google Drive search
- "check Figma" → activates Figma context
- "full context" → activates all plugins regardless of mode

## Performance Notes
- Fix mode should feel instant
- Build mode will be slower but comprehensive
- Design mode prioritizes visual/UX context over data
- Architecture mode balances speed with strategic thinking
- Cache invalidation happens when plugins load fresh data



